[
    {
        "content": "<p>should <code>|&gt;</code> be indented by the formatter? Here are two alternative ways to format it: (using <a href=\"https://github.com/rtfeldman/roc/blob/f4c0925b21afcb46fd6bd0315b19ee97d942a8f8/examples/json/ParserCore.roc\">this</a> as an example)</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"F#\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">jsonNumArray</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">jsonNum</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">sepBy</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">','</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">between</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">'['</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">']'</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"F#\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">jsonNumArray</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">jsonNum</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">sepBy</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">','</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">between</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">'['</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">']'</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>The first way (no indentation) is how <a href=\"https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/fsharp/language-reference/functions/#pipelines\">F# formats it</a> and also how <a href=\"https://medium.com/@rgulans/agresive-piping-in-elixir-37f535ad4ac1\">Elixir formats it</a>.</p>\n<p>Elm indents it, but I happen to know that that's because when <code>elm-format</code> was originally created, infix operators were a userspace thing and it treated them all the same (so it would indent both <code>|&gt;</code> and <code>+</code> the same way, because they're both arbitrary infix operators)</p>",
        "id": 288975026,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1657303983
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I can see some pros and cons to either</p>",
        "id": 288975076,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1657304008
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Personally, I find the first formatting easier to read</p>",
        "id": 288975222,
        "sender_full_name": "Ayaz Hafiz",
        "timestamp": 1657304076
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Despite being used to indenting <code>|&gt;</code> I think I'd prefer the first example as well.</p>",
        "id": 288975255,
        "sender_full_name": "Martin Stewart",
        "timestamp": 1657304097
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>two reasons that lead me to rethink whether defaulting to the way Elm does it is correct here (as Roc frequently does!) are:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>It's indented more, but it still seems very easy to me to tell what's going on in either version. So arguably it's causing things to be excessively indented unnecessarily.</li>\n<li>when you start a pipeline with a very short name, it doesn't look great in the mandatory-indentation version. e.g. compare:</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"F#\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">jsonNumArray</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">it</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">sepBy</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">','</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">between</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">'['</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">']'</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"F#\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">jsonNumArray</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">it</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">sepBy</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">','</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">between</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">'['</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">']'</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 288975312,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1657304129
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think if we do that, we should definitely automatically insert a blank line after the pipeline in defs</p>",
        "id": 288975451,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1657304193
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>e.g. the formatter shouldn't permit this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"F#\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">jsonNumArray</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">sepBy</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">','</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">between</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">'['</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">']'</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bar</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">sepBy</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">','</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">between</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">'['</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">']'</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">baz</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 288975532,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1657304239
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>instead, it should reformat to:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"F#\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">jsonNumArray</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">sepBy</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">','</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">between</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">'['</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">']'</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bar</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">sepBy</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">','</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">between</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">'['</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">']'</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">baz</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 288975551,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1657304253
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>or perhaps even:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"F#\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">jsonNumArray</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">sepBy</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">','</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">between</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">'['</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">']'</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">bar</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">sepBy</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">','</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">between</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">'['</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">']'</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">baz</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 288975600,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1657304277
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"281383\">Richard Feldman</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/304641-ideas/topic/indentation.20for.20.7C.3E/near/288975600\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>or perhaps even:</p>\n<p><div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"F#\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">jsonNumArray</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">sepBy</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">','</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">between</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">'['</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">']'</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">bar</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">sepBy</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">','</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">between</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">'['</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scalar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"sc\">']'</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">baz</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div><br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I think this example looks best</p>",
        "id": 288975730,
        "sender_full_name": "Martin Stewart",
        "timestamp": 1657304333
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>a related question is whether other infix operators should be indented the same way</p>",
        "id": 288975826,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1657304390
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>for example, <a href=\"https://github.com/rtfeldman/roc/blob/1a515b4bd0232a7d61eca5f8f4e093598286ebf5/examples/interactive/cli-platform/Url.roc#L193\">this</a> could be formatted as either:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elixir\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">if</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">byte</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&gt;=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">97</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;&amp;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">byte</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&lt;=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">122</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\"># lowercase ASCII</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">||</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">byte</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&gt;=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">65</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;&amp;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">byte</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&lt;=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">90</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\"># uppercase ASCII</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">||</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">byte</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&gt;=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">48</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;&amp;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">byte</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&lt;=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">57</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\"># digit</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"n\">then</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>or </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elixir\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">if</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">byte</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&gt;=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">97</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;&amp;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">byte</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&lt;=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">122</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\"># lowercase ASCII</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">||</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">byte</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&gt;=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">65</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;&amp;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">byte</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&lt;=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">90</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\"># uppercase ASCII</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">||</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">byte</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&gt;=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">48</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;&amp;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">byte</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&lt;=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">57</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\"># digit</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n<span class=\"n\">then</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 288975925,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1657304424
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>and same with <code>+</code>, <code>-</code>, etc.</p>",
        "id": 288975993,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1657304481
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>once again, I can see arguments either way! <span aria-label=\"big smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f604\" role=\"img\" title=\"big smile\">:big_smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 288976009,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1657304492
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I could go either way on those. Though maybe for consistency with <code>|&gt;</code> other operators shouldn't be indented either?</p>",
        "id": 288976126,
        "sender_full_name": "Martin Stewart",
        "timestamp": 1657304551
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>an interesting argument for not indenting <code>|&gt;</code> that just occurred to me: the operator works differently in Roc and Elm (in Roc it pipes the first argument; in Elm it pipes the last argument), so having a visual distinction if you're working in a code base that has both Roc and Elm code could be a nice reminder of which one you're dealing with!</p>",
        "id": 288976427,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1657304730
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Do F# and Elixir pipe the first argument?</p>",
        "id": 288977021,
        "sender_full_name": "jan kili",
        "timestamp": 1657305022
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Roc and Elixir do it the same way, and F# and Elm do it the same way</p>",
        "id": 288977266,
